# LiveKit voice (frontend)

Read `docs/architecture.md` (Web voice, Architectural decisions) first.

Worker-side STT/TTS and barge-in: agent API repo `docs/architecture.md` (LiveKit section) if in workspace — see `.cursorrules`.

## Room naming (`lib/livekit/room.ts`)

- Base prefix: `web-`
- **Each voice connect:** `web-{sessionId}--{connectionId}` via `livekitVoiceRoomName()`
- Pass `participantMetadata: sessionId` to `useSession` so token route resolves the chat thread
- **Do not** reuse the same room name after disconnect — LiveKit will not re-dispatch the agent

## Session lifecycle (`chat-panel.tsx`)

- `useSession` lives for the `sessionId` lifetime (not mounted only when voice is on)
- On voice enable: new `voiceConnectionId` (`crypto.randomUUID()`), then effect runs `start()`
- After `start()`: `await session.room.startAudio()` for browser autoplay unlock
- On voice disable / cleanup: `endVoiceSession()` → `voice_mode_exit` on `voice_control`, brief settle, then `end()`
- **Do not** mount/unmount `useSession` on the voice toggle

## Transcript sync (`voice-chat-sync.ts`)

Data topic: `chat_sync`

| Payload type | UI action |
|--------------|-----------|
| `voice_user` | `addVoiceMessage({ id: turnId, role: user, … })` |
| `voice_assistant` | `addVoiceMessage({ id: turnId-assistant, role: assistant, … })` |

This is the **source of truth** for voice rows in the chat list. `useSessionMessages` / `userTranscript` is live preview only (“Hearing: …”).

## Agents UI wrappers

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `agent-session-provider.tsx` | `SessionProvider` + `RoomAudioRenderer` |
| `start-audio-button.tsx` | LiveKit `StartAudio` fallback |
| `agent-audio-visualizer-bar.tsx` | `BarVisualizer` when agent speaks |

Render `AgentSessionProvider` only while `voiceEnabled` (children need session context).

## Token route (`api/livekit/token`)

- `sessionId` from `participantMetadata` before parsing room name suffix
- `RoomConfiguration` metadata + agent dispatch on every mint

## Do not

- Duplicate `PersonalAgent` or scheduling logic in the frontend
- Populate chat history from room transcriptions or partial STT events
- Skip new `voiceConnectionId` on voice re-enable
